Updated getNBackLevel() to map difficulty 1-10 across N-back levels 1 through 5 (was capped at 3). New mapping: difficulty 1-2 → 1-back, 3-4 → 2-back, 5-6 → 3-back, 7-8 → 4-back, 9-10 → 5-back. Also added 'export' to getNBackLevel, generateBalancedSequence, and isMatch so they can be tested as pure functions. The adaptive difficulty service already supports difficulty values up to 10, so no backend changes are needed — the higher difficulty values now correctly map to 4-back and 5-back in the frontend. All UI text, instructions, and scoring already used the dynamic 'n' variable, so they handle levels 4 and 5 without additional changes.